# H5X Binary & Addresses

Game directory: `G:\__H5__\H5Xdev`. Executables are located in the `bin` subfolder.
Target binary: **H5X.exe** (ToE 3.1 based). Image base `0x00400000`. Ghidra project: `h5x-ghidra-mcp/H5X.rep`.

**Critical:** Ghidra VAs match **H5X.exe only**, not vanilla `H5_Game.exe` (different section layout).

## PE sections

| Section | VA start | Virtual size | Raw offset |
|---|---|---|---|
| `.text` | `0x00001000` | `0x00A09000` | `0x00000400` |
| `.rdata` | `0x00A0A000` | `0x00115000` | `0x00A08600` |
| `.data` | `0x00B1F000` | `0x001CB000` | `0x00B1C800` |

File offset for `.text`: `file_offset = VA - 0x400C00`.

## Patching conventions

- All patch targets are **absolute VAs** in the game process (runtime memory patching).
- Use `VirtualProtect` before writes; see `mainH5.cpp` apply loop.
- `addresses.txt` is the developer RVA/function reference; cross-check with Ghidra for H5X.exe.
- Named Ghidra functions use `func_*` prefix; do not rename existing labels when doing RE.
